---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import SectionWrapper from '../components/SectionWrapper.astro';
import CTAButton from '../components/CTAButton.astro';
import VideoCard from '../components/VideoCard.astro';

const videos = await getCollection('videos');
---

<BaseLayout
  title="DeepWeave — Business Process Visibility"
  description="A navigable map of how your organisation actually works. Built by Saige."
>
  <Hero
    headline="You have an org chart. You don't have a map."
    subline="DeepWeave builds the operational picture your org chart doesn't show — who does what, what triggers what, and what breaks if it changes."
  />

  <SectionWrapper>
    <h2>The Problem</h2>
    <p>
      Every restructure, ERP implementation, or acquisition runs into the same wall: no one
      actually knows how the business works. Not in writing. Not in a form you can navigate. The
      knowledge lives in people's heads, distributed across roles and teams, invisible until
      something goes wrong.
    </p>
    <p>
      Consultants charge months of workshops to surface it. Most of the time, they don't get it
      right anyway.
    </p>
  </SectionWrapper>

  <SectionWrapper>
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <ol class="prose-list">
      <li><strong>Employees do a 15-minute recorded interview.</strong> Questions are designed to surface actual day-to-day work — no process expertise required.</li>
      <li><strong>AI processes the transcripts.</strong> Relationships, dependencies, and process ownership are inferred automatically.</li>
      <li><strong>The map appears.</strong> A navigable visual network — roles, processes, and the threads connecting them. Click any node to see the work underneath it.</li>
    </ol>
  </SectionWrapper>

  <SectionWrapper narrow>
    <h2>What You Have At The End</h2>
    <p>A living operational map. Not a slide deck. Not a report that dates the moment it's printed.</p>
    <p>
      You can see which processes exist, who owns them, what they depend on, and where the
      risks are. The kind of clarity that used to take months — available before the project starts.
    </p>
    <p>
      Built for the moments that demand it: ERP implementations, restructures, mergers and
      acquisitions, and any transformation where understanding the current state is the
      prerequisite to changing it.
    </p>
  </SectionWrapper>

  <SectionWrapper narrow>
    <p>
      DeepWeave is a product of Saige — a company being built around a single idea: that
      operational knowledge shouldn't be locked inside people's heads. More to come.
    </p>
  </SectionWrapper>

  {videos.length > 0 && (
    <SectionWrapper>
      <div class="video-grid">
        {videos.map((video) => (
          <VideoCard
            title={video.data.title}
            date={video.data.date}
            url={video.data.url}
            description={video.data.description}
          />
        ))}
      </div>
    </SectionWrapper>
  )}

  <SectionWrapper>
    <div class="closing-cta">
      <p>Interested in early access or a conversation about what this could do for your organisation?</p>
      <CTAButton href="mailto:joshua@joshuawilson.co.nz" label="Get in touch" />
    </div>
  </SectionWrapper>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  h2 {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  p + p {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .prose-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .prose-list li {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .prose-list li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .video-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .closing-cta {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .closing-cta p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .video-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
